Our project aims to explore the effects of climate change on marine ecosystems. We will conduct a comprehensive study of the changes in temperature, acidity, and s alinity levels of the oceans and their impact on the biodiversity of marine life. To achieve this, we will collect and analyze data from various sources, including satellite imagery, ocean sensors, and field surveys. We will also examine the role of human activities such as overfishing, pollution, and habitat destruction on the decline of marine species. Our team will work closely with local communities and policymakers to raise awareness of the urgent need to protect our oceans and develop sustainable practices. Throughout the project, we will utilize advanced technologies and data analytics to gain insights into the complex interactions between climate change, human activities , and marine ecosystems. By doing so, we hope to contribute to the scientific communit y's understanding of the environmental challenges we face and pave the way for a more s ustainable future.
